Ameron Inc said its boardadopted a rights plan designed to protect shareholders frompotentially unfair takeover tactics.    The plan calls for distribution of one right for each ofits outstanding common shares and each right entitles theholder to buy one/one-hundredth of a share of newly authorizedSeries A Junior Participating cumulative Preferred stock at anexercise price of 55 dlrs, Ameron said.    It said the rights are exercisable if a group acquires 20pct or more of its common stock or announces a tender offer for30 pct or more of its shares. Reuter&#3;